# Raspberri_Pi_Audio (Pi + Behringer UCA202 + OLED)

Local clone: `/home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio`. Python venv: `.venv/` (numpy, sounddevice, luma.oled, pillow). System: `libportaudio2` for PortAudio.

GitHub: `https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio`

## User workflow (Cursor / Agent)

- Prefer **not** asking the user to copy-paste shell commands into an external terminal.
- When testing or running demos, the **coding agent should propose the exact terminal command** so the user can approve with **Run** / **OK** on the prompt.
- **Git / GitHub:** the agent carries work **up to a Pull Request that is ready to merge** (branch on `origin` + PR link). The user opens the **PR**, reviews **Files changed** / **Commits**, and clicks **Merge pull request** when satisfied. The agent does **not** click **Merge** on GitHub.

## Git: agent prepares the PR; you merge on GitHub (required)

**End state:** a **Pull request** page like `https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/pull/<N>` where the user can review everything and use **Merge pull request** when ready (example: [PR #1](https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/pull/1)). When branch rules protect `main`, new work reaches `main` only through that merge.

### Agent responsibilities (in order)

1. **Branch:** put new work on **`wip/<topic>`** or **`feature/<topic>`** when using the PR workflow (not new commits only on `main` if `main` is protected).
2. **Commit** with a clear message; post **`git log -1 --oneline`**, **`git show --stat`**, and **`git rev-parse HEAD`**.
3. **Push the head branch to `origin`** (feature branch only — **do not** push new work straight to **`origin/main`** when the workflow is PR-only):
   - e.g. `git push -u origin HEAD` on `wip/...`, or `git push -u origin HEAD:wip/<topic>` when using a one-off remote branch name.
4. **Ensure a PR exists** and send the **`/pull/N`** link:
   - **Preferred:** `gh pr create --base main --head wip/<topic> --title "..." --body "..."` when `gh` is installed and authenticated.
   - **Fallback:** compare (opens **Create pull request** with the right range):  
     `https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/compare/main...wip/<topic>?expand=1`
   - **Fallback 2:** new PR form:  
     `https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/pull/new/wip/<topic>`

### User responsibilities

1. Open the **PR** link from the agent.
2. Review **Commits** and **Files changed**.
3. Click **Merge pull request** (and confirm) when satisfied.
4. On the Pi: **`git checkout main && git pull origin main`** after merge so local `main` matches GitHub.

### Rules

- **Do not** merge on GitHub as the agent; that stays with the user.
- **Do not** land changes on **`origin/main`** by direct push when the agreed workflow is PR-only; use **`wip/...`** + PR.
- After commits, always post stats and the **handoff** link (PR URL preferred; otherwise compare / `pull/new`).

