## Branch protection: require PR for `main` (GitHub)

Goal: **no direct pushes of new commits to `main`** — changes land via a **pull request** (still mergeable by you as repo owner unless you add stricter review rules).

### Option A — GitHub website (no API)

1. Open: `https://github.com/jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/settings/rules`
2. **New ruleset** (or **New branch ruleset** depending on UI).
3. **Name:** e.g. `protect-main-pr-only`.
4. **Enforcement status:** Active.
5. **Target branches:** restrict to `main` (or “Default branch” if that is `main`).
6. Enable **Require a pull request before merging**.
7. **Required approvals:** set to **0** if you work solo and only want the PR gate (no second human). Use **1+** if you want mandatory reviews.
8. Save. Confirm `main` no longer accepts fast-forward-only pushes of new work without a PR.

GitHub docs: [About rulesets](https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/configuring-branches-and-merges-in-your-repository/managing-rulesets/about-rules-for-repositories).

### Option B — API script (Pi or PC; needs PAT once)

Repo script: [`scripts/enable-main-ruleset.sh`](/home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/scripts/enable-main-ruleset.sh)

```bash
export GH_TOKEN=ghp_xxxx   # classic PAT with `repo`, or fine-grained with Administration: write
bash /home/uzan/Raspberri_Pi_Audio/scripts/enable-main-ruleset.sh
```

Optional: `APPROVALS=1` for one required approving review. If creation fails with **422**, a ruleset with the same name may already exist — remove or rename it in **Settings → Rules**.

REST reference: [Create a repository ruleset](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/repos/rules?apiVersion=2022-11-28#create-a-repository-ruleset).

### Notes

- **Agents cannot click GitHub Settings for you**; they can propose the script or paste the links above. Turning the rule on is **always** on GitHub (UI or API with your token).
- After protection is on, day-to-day flow: work on `feature/...` or `wip/...` → open **PR into `main`** → merge when ready.

## Hardware notes

- Input device name match in code: `USB Audio CODEC` (Behringer UCA202 class).
- OLED: I2C bus `1`, address `0x3C`, driver `sh1106` via `luma.oled`.
- If the visualizer shows **NO SIGNAL**, raise the **analog** source level into the RCA line-in (software RMS gate is similar to the BPM script).
